An Act to require liability insurance for gun ownership.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 140 of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding the following section:-
2 Section 207. (a) Whoever possess, carries, or owns a firearm, rifle or shotgun without a
3 liability policy or bond or deposit required by the provisions of this chapter which has not been
4 provided and maintained in accordance therewith shall be punished by a fine of not less than five
5 hundred nor more than five thousand dollars or by imprisonment for not more than one year in a
6 house of correction, or both such fine and imprisonment. This section shall not apply to a person
7 who possesses a firearm, rifle, or shotgun on a temporary basis while on the premises of a
8 licensed gun club.
9 (b) The commissioner of insurance shall promulgate regulations set forth for the
10 minimum terms of liability insurance policies which shall satisfy the requirements of this section.
